Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{¼%tsp for the breadcrumbs} and @water{2%tbsp for the breadcrumbs}, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the way through).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Halfway through cooking the onion, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once the onion is golden, add the @sugar{½%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, pop the meatballs onto a large baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the meatballs have 2-3 mins left, pop the buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Move the wedges to the bottom shelf of your oven.

Once cooked, remove the meatballs from the baking tray and wipe the tray clean. Add the warmed buns to the tray and spread with the @burger sauce{30%g}. Share the meatballs between the buns and top with the cheese.

Bake on the top shelf until the cheese is melted and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer the meatball subs to your plates and serve the wedges alongside.

Spoon the caramelised onion on top of the meatball subs to finish.

Enjoy!